title: Graduating Class
text: Pictured is a MHS graduating class, most likely the class of 1903. You can see that in 1903, class size was much smaller than it is today. What else looks different from today?

title: Classrooms
text: Snapped in 1940, this photograph shows students hard at work in an industrial arts class inside the MHS building. Visit our Life at MHS features to learn more about student life.

title: Play
text: In 1940, students play outside the new MHS. To learn more about the residential area that once existed where they play, visit our Map feature.

title: 1980s Students
text: In front of the MHS entrance in the 1980s, two students beam at the camera in a glimpse into life in the past. To learn more about student life at MHS, click ‘Student Life’ button.

title: Things We Found
text: The things we found are, in essence, things people have used, made or owned in the past and even into the present. Explore the knowledge shared by the people of Moscow for this exhibit, and thus, for the people of Moscow, too.

title: Paper
text: Here you can see that the "artifacts" from MHS may include things that are very familiar, such as a scrap of paper with math equations scribbled on it. Explore this further in the "Artifact Catalog" and the "Life at MHS" pages.

title: School Supplies
text: Remember this? School supplies made up a large portion of what archaeologists found on the MHS property. Explore the "Life at MHS" page to learn more about what activities students were doing at school!

title: Plate or Bowl?
text: Students, staff, and faculty have to eat, and they always have! Fragments of dishes, like this one pictured, were found all over the school property. The green mark indicates that the dish was produced in France by the Haviland & CIE. company between 1894 and 1931.
